Sentencas: A two-dimensional model of nickel/yttria-stabilized zirconia (Ni/YSZ) solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC), was developed for a button cell system.
Titulo: A two-dimensional modeling of solid oxide fuel cell button cells with detailed electrochemistry mechanism

Sentencas: The model integrates the detailed catalytic, electrochemical elementary reactions with ionic/electronic conduction and multiple gas transport processes in SOFC.
Titulo: A two-dimensional modeling of solid oxide fuel cell button cells with detailed electrochemistry mechanism

Sentencas: The model is validated using published experimental data for H-2-H2O fuel gas under different cell sizes and operating conditions.
Titulo: A two-dimensional modeling of solid oxide fuel cell button cells with detailed electrochemistry mechanism

Sentencas: The distributions of gas/surface phase species concentration and current density were predicted and the effects of operating temperature, fuel gas composition and fuel channel tube design on the cell performance were studied.
Titulo: A two-dimensional modeling of solid oxide fuel cell button cells with detailed electrochemistry mechanism

Sentencas: The results show that the electrochemical reaction processes occurs mainly within a 20 mu m distance from the anode/electrolyte interface and that the Ni catalyst surface is covered mainly by H(s).
Titulo: A two-dimensional modeling of solid oxide fuel cell button cells with detailed electrochemistry mechanism

Sentencas: For the chamber channel design, the calculations show that the tube chamber should have a diameter no smaller than the cathode electrode to obtain the best SOFC performance.
Titulo: A two-dimensional modeling of solid oxide fuel cell button cells with detailed electrochemistry mechanism
